In [ ]:
sn = 1  #   
en = 101  #101#   

time = TicToc()
time.tic()
for k in range(sn,en):
    data0 = train[train.==k]
    train_y = data0.
    train_X = data0.drop([''], axis = 1)

    num_columns = train_X.select_dtypes('number').columns.tolist()
    cat_columns = train_X.select_dtypes('object').columns.tolist()

    cat_preprocess = make_pipeline( OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown="ignore", sparse_output=False) )
    num_preprocess = make_pipeline( StandardScaler() )

    drop_cols = [""]
    num_columns = [c for c in num_columns if c not in drop_cols]

    preprocess = ColumnTransformer([
        ("num", num_preprocess, num_columns),
        ("cat", cat_preprocess, cat_columns),
        ("drop", "drop", drop_cols),  
    ])

    reg_pipe = Pipeline([
        ("preprocess", preprocess ),
        ("regressor", xgb.XGBRegressor())
    ])
    #   :  
    sqrt_y = FunctionTransformer(func=np.sqrt, inverse_func=np.square, validate=True)
    
    model = TransformedTargetRegressor(  
        regressor   = reg_pipe,           
        transformer = sqrt_y
    )

    Xgb_param = {'regressor__regressor__learning_rate': np.arange(0.01, 0.3, 0.05)}

    cv = KFold(n_splits = 5, shuffle = True, random_state = 0)
    Xgb_search = GridSearchCV(estimator = model,
                              param_grid = Xgb_param,
                              cv = cv,
                              scoring = 'neg_root_mean_squared_error')
    Xgb_search.fit(train_X, train_y)
    
    test_X = test[test.==k]
    pred = Xgb_search.predict(test_X)
    #pred_all = pred_all.extend(pred.tolist() )
    if k==1:
        pred_all = pred
    else:
        pred_all = np.concatenate([pred_all, pred])      
    print(k)
    
time.toc()
